javadoc.text: * The job the singular value solvers are to do. This only limits which singular vectors * are computed, all the singular values are always computed
* Compute all of the singular vectors
* Do not compute any singular vectors
* Overwrite passed data. For an M*N matrix, this either overwrites the * passed matrix with as many singular vectors as there is room for. Details depend on * the actual algorithm
* Compute parts of the singular vectors. For an M*N matrix, this * computes min(M,N) singular vectors
